	(74,15,'Director of Project Management Department (01 post)','<ul>\r\n<li>Define overall governance process of project management across the company.</li>\r\n<li>Track, analyze, and report progress of key project portfolio.</li>\r\n<li>Coordinate across key stakeholders to ensure effective changes and collaboration in the organization.</li>\r\n<li>Manage communication across organization to support programs or project implementation; including presentation to stakeholders throughout project cycle.</li>\r\n<li>Undertake different role(s) within project management. Depending on nature of each project: 1). Primary role is to lead/manage transformative project to align with corporate strategic direction; the role requires end-to-&nbsp; end management of project delivery which include business development, activity planning, risk/benefit identification, cross functional coordination, and effective project closure monitoring. 2). As and when required, perform business analyst role to support functional teams.</li>\r\n<li>Foster a collaborative working environment with functional teams.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Degree in business or related field is preferred, MBA is preferred</li>\r\n<li>Good proficiency in MS. Office including Ms. Excel , Ms. PowerPoint</li>\r\n<li>At least 7 years experiences, including 2 years in management position &amp; 3-5 years in project management or relevant experiences</li>\r\n<li>Experience in managing operational or structural change within an organization and knowledge and experience on digital technology is a plus</li>\r\n<li>Sound working knowledge of general business process and organizational framework such as goals, strategy, culture and structure</li>\r\n<li>Be very good in verbal and written English</li>\r\n<li>Good time management skills and ability to multi-task</li>\r\n<li>Strong sense of urgency with high level of commitment and determination to deliver a great result</li>\r\n<li>Ability to monitor process/facilitate progress 