	(172,15,'Manager of Public Relation - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Develop the PR plan and strategic of HKL in accordance with company vision, mission and strategy.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Identify the tactic in order to bring HKL&rsquo;s brand into public which can ensure the consistency &amp; positive image appears in all media types.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Build good relationship with media partners broadcasting HKL &amp; ensure its positive brand image in all the time.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Promote all product/services of HKL to ensure that they are recognized &amp; understand by external audience.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Develop and manage policy, framework and process for both internal &amp; external communication, internal communication activities plan, and channel &amp; execute them across all the functions within HKL.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Initiate to develop and implement activities in order to strengthen relationship and HKL&rsquo;s core value among HKL employee.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Manage the HKL communication message and new pipelines, and then follow the feedback.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Work as copy write copy of HKL&rsquo;s message, ads, brochures, TV spots, radio, and other forms of advertising.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Manage to support PR activities in relate with photography and video record for using in press release or other communication channel.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Support for internal &amp; external activities and other tasks assigned by supervisor.</span></li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Bachelor degree in marketing, Journalism or related majors in business administration</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Understanding of banking and microfinance sector, especially bank/MFI product and service</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">At least 2 years experiences in marketing, journalism or event organizing</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Having solid project management skills</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Good public speaking and presentation skills</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">High proficiency in writing, speaking, reading and listening English</span><span style=\"font-size: larger;\"><span style=\"color: #0000ff;\"><strong><br /></strong></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>',1,36,15,'1','06/18/2018',0,NULL,9,5,4,'English','2018-06-01 12:36:59','2018-06-01 12:36:59'),
	(173,15,'Manager of Branding - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Develop brand guidelines, brand vision and value proposition for short and long term.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Maintain and enhance brand policies and procedure such as Corporate Identity by ensuring all stakeholders adopt and use it correctly.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Actively promote HKL brand by ensuring all projects/programs meet corporate brand standards.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Manage all the activities stipulated in the brand plan to ensure that brand objectives are achieved.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Manage and track material effectiveness in order to modify and improve promotion development.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Quality checks marketing material at all stages of development and production process, applies changes where required, and provides final approval to ensure quality, finished material being produced.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Work closely with research team for competitor and customer insights analysis, brand preference and brand consideration survey.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Work with marketing and communication team for plan and execution of all communications and media actions as well as create promotional campaign.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Perform other tasks assigned by direct supervisor.</span></li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Bachelor degree in Business Administration, Marketing, or other related field, master degree is preferable.</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">At least 2 years working experiences specializing in marketing and branding.</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Strong conceptualization and analytical skills and capacity to pro-actively plan and well-implementation.</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Well understand about financial institution environment, experience with bank is preferable.</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Good interpersonal communication, presentation skill, team work, result-oriented.</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Excellent skill in MS Office includes Word, Excel, and Power Point.</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">High proficiency in writing, speaking, reading and listening English</span></span></li>\r\n</ul>',1,36,15,'1','06/17/2018',0,NULL,9,5,4,'English','2018-06-01 12:39:53','2018-06-01 12:39:53'),
	(174,16,'ICT Service Officer - 06 posts','<ul class=\"bullet-red\">\r\n<li>Assign CIT service officers for cash in transit to ATMs, NBC, ABA branches and other banks;</li>\r\n<li>Implementation of proper communication with cash department for amount of cash and numbers of trips for daily CIT operation;</li>\r\n<li>Implementation of checking and maintenance CIT card;</li>\r\n<li>Inspection of CIT service equipment of CIT service officer beofre leaving for CIT trip;</li>\r\n<li>Monitoring and receiving CIT trip status from CIT service officers via radio communication</li>\r\n<li>Make report of daily CIT trips into CITService Log book;</li>\r\n<li>Conducting of screening of pamanent CIT service officers;</li>\r\n<li>Assign CIT service officer to escort refinancing team as per instruction from head of security or CIT supervisor;</li>\r\n<li>Checking status of escorting refinancing team from CIT service officers via radio communication;</li>\r\n<li>Observation and investigation of CIT service officers who suspected breach of CIT policy;</li>\r\n<li>Observation and collecting information of ABA staff who breach code of conduct, bank policies and who suspected commited fraud;</li>\r\n<li>Assist CIT service supervisor to do other tasks.</li>\r\n<li>Arrangement of schedule and assign CIT service officers to safeguard ABA head offices on working hours, weekend, day off and public holidays;;</li>\r\n<li>Arrangement of schedule and assign CIT service officers to spot check security guards of security agencies who safeguard for ABA branches in PP;</li>\r\n<li>Assign CIT service officers to protect ABA branches in PP as per instruction from head of security.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul class=\"bullet-red\">\r\n<li>Bachelor Degree.</li>\r\n<li>CIT skill.</li>\r\n<li>Security skill.</li>\r\n<li>Basic bodyguard skill.</li>\r\n<li>Basic investigation skill.</li>\r\n<li>Computer (Microsoft word and Excel).</li>\r\n<li>At least 2 years with security field and CIT tasks.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,59,7,'6','07/15/2018',0,NULL,3,5,9,'English','2018-06-02 09:56:34','2018-07-15 09:44:22'),
	(175,15,'Team Leader of Fraud Management - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Coordinate and planning organizing leading and controlling the staff under supervisor to proactively in identify possible fraud incidents that are relevant to HKL.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Assist risk owner on how to manage fraud in accordance with fraud management policies.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Involve with the relevant business unit to conduct the fraud risk assessment on new business initiative/service/policy procedure and product development&hellip;etc.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Maintain the recording mechanism of the fraud register, fraud incident report register and database as well as the fraud control plan.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Assist the director of produce the dashboard report and other monthly monitoring report as required.&nbsp;</span></li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Bachelor degree of Management, Banking and Finance, Economics, or other related field, English degree is preferable.</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Self-motivation and able to manage own workload.</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">At least 1 year experience in field fraud management, risk management, audit compliance.</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Be flexible with working hours.</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Computer literacy in MS Office includes Word, Excel, Power Point, Internet and Email.</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Good communication in Khmer and English.</span></span></li>\r\n</ul>',1,41,7,'1','06/15/2018',0,NULL,7,5,11,'English','2018-06-02 10:00:44','2018-06-02 10:00:44'),
	(176,16,'ATM/CIM Officer - 06 posts','<ul class=\"bullet-red\">\r\n<li>Load cash to&nbsp; ATM cassette after verify and run with machine.</li>\r\n<li>All ATM cash refill are recorded serial number and correct amount in hopper.</li>\r\n<li>Manage ATM hopper in transit.</li>\r\n<li>Support to ATM cash management supervisor for verifying actual cash with receipt of ATM remaining.</li>\r\n<li>Monitor ATM error and collect the reason of error, ATM maintenance and ATM removing.</li>\r\n<li>Make sure ATM hopper input with the right position.</li>\r\n<li>Run &amp; verify cash from ATM/cash-in Kiosk machine&nbsp; with senior officer at office.</li>\r\n<li>Collect cash from cash-in Kiosk machine.</li>\r\n<li>Monitor Kiosk error and collect the reason of error,&nbsp; maintenance and removing.</li>\r\n<li>Sort new bill for ATM.</li>\r\n<li>Other task assigned by supervisor/ manager.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul class=\"bullet-red\">\r\n<li>Completed high school or bachelor degree in Business, Finance and Banking, Accounting or any related fields.</li>\r\n<li>High attention to details and accuracy.</li>\r\n<li>Good customer service skills.</li>\r\n<li>Ability to work effectively in a team environment.</li>\r\n<li>Good organizational skills.</li>\r\n<li>Acceptable written and verbal communication skills (Khmer and English )Good computer literacy.\r\n<h3>Location</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"bullet-red\">\r\n<li>Mao Seng tung Branch, Phnom Penh&nbsp; (2 posts)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Siem Reap Branch (1 post)&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Toul Kork Branch (1 post)</li>\r\n<li>Stung mean Chey branch, Phnom Penh (1 post)</li>\r\n<li>Central Market Branch, Phnom Penh, (1 post)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>',1,59,15,'6','06/10/2018',0,NULL,7,5,9,'English','2018-06-02 10:02:42','2018-06-02 10:02:42'),
	(177,16,'Database Administrator - 01 post','<ul class=\"bullet-red\">\r\n<li>Installation and updating of new software &ndash; install new versions of oracle database software, oracle application software, core banking application (Flexcube) and other software related to oracle administration.</li>\r\n<li>Maintenance of database servers, core banking application servers and related servers.</li>\r\n<li>Controlling access permissions and privileges of databases.</li>\r\n<li>Maintaining secure storage of databases backup. &nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Troubleshooting any oracle database problems.</li>\r\n<li>Ensuring maximum uptime.</li>\r\n<li>Ensuring maximum performance.</li>\r\n<li>Restoring database to testing environment (UAT).</li>\r\n<li>Development and testing support &ndash; helping programmer and software engineers to efficiently utilize the database. &nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Responsible for documenting the configuration of database and troubleshooting scenario.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul class=\"bullet-red\">\r\n<li>Bachelor degree in Information Technology, Computer Science or related field.</li>\r\n<li>Minimum of 1 year experience as DBA or in banking sector.</li>\r\n<li>Holding Oracle Database Administrator Certified Associate is preferable.</li>\r\n<li>Experience with Linux System Administration.</li>\r\n<li>Must be available to work night time shift.</li>\r\n<li>Be honest, quick learner, flexible and punctual.</li>\r\n<li>Willing to work as a team.</li>\r\n<li>Willing to learn new technology and more self-motivation and self-study.</li>\r\n<li>Good English and Khmer communication (both written and spoken).</li>\r\n<li>Able to work longer hours under minimum supervision and under pressure.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,59,15,'1','06/10/2018',0,NULL,7,5,11,'English','2018-06-02 10:04:27','2018-06-02 10:04:27'),
	(178,15,'Operational Risk Management - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Coordinate the implementation plan with key relevant stakeholder to proactively in identifying operational risk incidents and potential risks that are relevant.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Assist risk owner on how to manage operational risks in accordance with operational risk policies procedure and create strategies for solution to response the operational risk incidents.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Involve with the relevant business unit to conduct the risk assessment on new business initiative/service/policy procedure and product development&hellip;etc.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Maintain the recording mechanism of the operational risk register, risk incident report register, operational loss event database and fraud control plan register.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Assist the Head of Operational Risk Unit to produce the dashboard design and business continuity planning for managing the unexpected risk event that could impact to the business operation of HKL.</span></li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Bachelor degree of Management, Banking and Finance, Economics, or other related field, English degree is preferable.</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">At least 1 year experience on operational risks and fraud risk management.</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Good understanding and knowledge of loan assessment process in advance. </span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Self-motivation and able to manage own workload.</span></span></li>