	(208,15,'Manager of Non Credit Product Development for Insurance - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Delivery the insurance products line accordance with the company&rsquo;s strategy within the estimate time frame.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Develop the sale strategies and implement to the market.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Regularly conduct market research and analysis to understand implications and identify new opportunities in line with institute\'s strategies and expansion plans.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Manage and monitor insurance team performance via good team work, motivation and coaching for high productivity and critical understanding.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Ensure end-to-end management of products and campaigns across channels.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Co-ordinate with key internal and external stakeholder groups, including existing clients to continuously growing of insurance business.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Deliver product governance and control such as partner\'s due diligence, product program review, business agreements, and service level agreements.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Analyzes cost &amp; benefit of insurance products, marketing or sale activities</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Prepares the budget plan projections for insurance product launch, sale or marketing campaign.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Perform others tasks assigned by supervisor.</span></li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Bachelor or Master Degree in banking/finance or business management, or related fields.</span></span></li>\r\n<li