	(220,15,'Branch Audit Officer for Credit Review - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Establishing the audit planning and budgeting to conduct internal auditing activities at branches of HKL.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Performing the audit procedures and execute the policies and procedures are being followed and properly implemented.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Reviews the existing HKL&rsquo;s policies and procedures, assess the quality of internal controls to ensure that HKL has adequate and prevented the risks fraudulent, and find out the control weakness or shortage. </span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Preparing an audit working paper and a draft audit report to team leader or supervisors for reviewing.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Identify the key risks regarding to the Credit review transactions to be included and developed the audit procedures, and participate in developing to improve the quality of internal audit&rsquo;s work.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Preparing pre-audit analysis checklist and posed engagement report.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Perform other tasks as require by management.</span></li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Bachelor degree of Audit, financial, banking, Business Management or Economics.</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Honest, reliable people</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Dynamic and pleasant personality</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Excellent interpersonal and verbal communication skills</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Highly acquainted with computer systems and programs, such MS Word, MS Excel, MS PowerPoint, Email &amp; Internet and core banking system is an advantage.</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Good Command written with English and Khmer. </span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Good analytical and problem-solving skills.</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Willing to work in the field (around 80% to 90% in the field work) including weekends.</span><span style=\"font-size: larger;\"><span style=\"color: #0000ff;\"><strong><br /></strong></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>',1,77,7,'1','06/30/2018',0,NULL,7,5,8,'English','2018-06-15 10:30:55','2018-06-15 10:30:55'),
	(221,15,'Finance Officer for Accounting and Checking - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Collect and follow up on accounting documents from branches promptly.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Check and analyze accounting documents of all assigned branches and try to find out the error for improvement. </span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Carefully keep accounting documents that were received from branches in safe place and in chronological order.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Explain the related Finance and Accounting policy and procedures to Chief Accountants on how to record transactions to the system and how to prepare the supporting documents. </span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Check documents if Branches adjust the transactions following comment on the summary mistake sent to branch.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Support to Chief Accountants and Accountants when there is request from Branch Manager.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Perform physical counting cash in ATM to confirm the accuracy of cash in ATM balance.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Other duties as required by supervisor</span></li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Bachelor degree in Accounting, Finance and banking, Economics, or other related fields.</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Good skill in MS Office includes Word, Excel and PowerPoint.</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Friendly, Flexible and can work under pressure.</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Good command of English is preferred.</span></span></li>\r\n</ul>',1,28,7,'1','06/30/2018',0,NULL,3,5,8,'English','2018-06-15 10:32:36','2018-06-15 10:32:36'),
	(222,19,'Application & Development Manager - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Plan for new system development in response to organization growth</li>\r\n<li>Design and develop MIS policies / procedures</li>\r\n<li>Supervise the day-to-day operations of the Information System and lead / manage software developers</li>\r\n<li>Manage the day-to-day operational and tactical aspects the MIS team to include decisions that ensure accurate and timely delivery of promised MIS services and projects</li>\r\n<li>Monitor work status and ensure that key activities and deliverables are completed as schedules and develop contingency or escalation plans for slipping tasks</li>\r\n<li>Ensure that all significant MIS activities can be managed by project management standards; regularly update project schedules, performance measures, and Standard Operating Procedures</li>\r\n<li>Review in-house software to standards and periodically make recommendations</li>\r\n<li>Maintain MIS staff by recruiting, selecting, orienting, and training employees; developing personal growth opportunities</li>\r\n<li>Enhance information systems results by identifying information systems technology opportunities and developing application strategies</li>\r\n<li>Must be able to perform duties with moderate to lower supervision</li>\r\n<li>Contribute to team effort by accomplishing related results as needed</li>\r\n<li>Provide constructive feedback on team members&rsquo; performance to team members</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Male/female, Cambodian nationality</li>\r\n<li>Bachelor degree in computer science or equivalent</li>\r\n<li>Minimum of 3 years of experience in the development, operation, and maintenance of enterprise information systems</li>\r\n<li>Experience with Java and Spring</li>\r\n<li>Experience leading a team to reach goals and objectives</li>\r\n<li>Ability to produce, execute, update, and manage work plans, progress reports, and other related documentation</li>\r\n<li>Proven track record of success in the development and day-to-day management of information system and projects</li>\r\n<li>Autonomous and proactive, quick learner, and effective communication</li>\r\n</ul>',1,59,15,'1','07/15/2018',0,1,9,5,4,'English','2018-06-15 16:15:35','2019-09-05 13:03:46'),
	(223,19,'Risk and Compliance Intern - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Assist in preparing Cash Transaction Report(CTR) and suspicious transaction report(STR)</li>\r\n<li>Keep updating AML/CFT knowledge from other sources (e-learning, training&hellip;)</li>\r\n<li>Assist in updating terrorist list, risk country list, political exposed person list, and deposit client risk assessment.</li>\r\n<li>Assist in preparing and sending the respond letters to NBC</li>\r\n<li>Keep understanding and updating FATCA</li>\r\n<li>Assist in risk assessment and risk facilitation</li>\r\n<li>Assist in registering risks and loss and incident cases</li>\r\n<li>Assist in trainings conducted by Risk and Compliance Department</li>\r\n<li>Perform other tasks assigned by Head of Risk and Compliance</li>\r\n<li>Independent judgment with strong analytical capacity and creative.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>4th year student in Business, Accounting, English or Law</li>\r\n<li>Willing to learn more with highly motivated and commitment</li>\r\n<li>Good command in English, both oral and written</li>\r\n<li>Proficient with Microsoft Word, Excel, and Power Point</li>\r\n<li>Willing to travel to work in the provinces(for mission)</li>\r\n<li>Independent judgment with strong analytical capacity and creative.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,39,7,'1','06/22/2018',0,NULL,2,5,1,'English','2018-06-15 16:18:37','2018-06-15 16:18:37'),
	(224,19,'Branch Credit Admin Officer - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Review Loan Document from Credit Officer before submit to Branch Manager and checking CBC.</li>\r\n<li>Check Client Credit History in CBC by follow the policy and procedure.</li>\r\n<li>Prepare and review loan document before submit Credit Committee.</li>\r\n<li>Review and re-check Loan Agreement, Hypothec Agreement, legal document, and Collateral/Security Documents before giving to customer to process with authority, disbursement, and filing.</li>\r\n<li>Control and monitor Credit Committee Loan minute approving which send by Senior SME Lending Support at Head Office.</li>\r\n<li>Help Branch Manager to share Memo, guideline, and follow up with users to ensure that they are compliance.</li>\r\n<li>Maintain customer information confidentiality.</li>\r\n<li>Record and track client&rsquo;s Collateral information into core banking system.</li>\r\n<li>Safe keeping all client&rsquo;s documents such as Client Information, Loan Document, and Collateral/Security Document by following policy and procedure.</li>\r\n<li>Coordinate related works with Credit Admin Office at Head Office.</li>\r\n<li>Others task as assign by supervisor.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor degree in the field of banking and finance, accounting, economic, law or other equivalent.</li>\r\n<li>At least 1-year experience in Microfinance/Bank.</li>\r\n<li>Have strong numeric and administrative skill.</li>\r\n<li>Negotiation and internal relationship building.</li>\r\n<li>Sound written and verbal English communication skills.</li>\r\n<li>Advanced Computer Skills (Ms. Word, Excel, and Power Point).</li>\r\n<li>Ability on problem solving and good communication skills.</li>\r\n<li>Good behavior committed and disciplined.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,41,7,'1','06/22/2018',0,NULL,3,5,11,'English','2018-06-15 16:21:05','2018-06-15 16:21:05');
