	(325,15,'Deputy Director of Credit and Market Risk Management - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Assist Credit and Market Risk Management to achieve the annual work plans, Department&rsquo;s objectives and HKL&rsquo;s goals.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Perform Credit portfolio management and portfolio quality analysis.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Provide Analysis and risk recommendations.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Deliver high quality data-driven analyses.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Identify and respond to analytics or data trends opportunities.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Manage Excute project indepently from end-to- end.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Overhaul and develop reqular reports.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Develop forecasting models to enhance.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Develop staistical credit risk models and credit score card.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Analyze on the credit concentration risk, propose and review credit limit exposure.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Performance other tasks as assigned by management.</span></li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Master&rsquo;s Degree with background of financial banking, Finance, Accounting, Economics, Statistic, Mathematics, Computer Science.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Work experience in different areas of bank and financial institution at least 5 years, including 3 year experience risk management.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Good understanding of the bank and Financial institution lending policies, Procedures and reasons or events of default.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Proven ability to translate operational and strategic challenges into data driven analysis enabling optimized decision making</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Experience in Statistical model development methodologies or statistical programming language is an advantage.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Strong quantitative, analytical, and problem-solving skills.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Strong leadership aptitude and ability to engage others in developing risk management capabilities.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Excellent command of Khmer and English.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Good with computer systems and programs, such MS Word, Advance MS Excel, MS PowerPoint, and core banking system is advantage.<span style=\"font-size: larger;\"><span style=\"color: #0000ff;\"><strong></strong></span></span></span></span>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Content, sans-serif; font-weight: 400; line-height: 1.1; color: #333333; margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 24px;\">Location</h3>\r\n<p class=\"bodytext\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #555555; font-family: Content, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; font-weight: 400;\">Head Office, Phnom Penh</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>',1,36,15,'1','08/16/2018',0,NULL,9,9,6,'English','2018-07-29 11:31:57','2018-07-29 11:31:57'),
	(326,16,'Bancassurance Specialist - 01 post','<ul class=\"bullet-red\">\r\n<li>Assist to evaluate each branch and individual referral performance to design the right quality training program to improve their performance</li>\r\n<li>Design onboard training new &amp; existing to officer &amp; senior officer level</li>\r\n<li>Motivation support to encourage staffs to collaborate with business partner to archive the same goal&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Develop good training presentation</li>\r\n<li>Arrange training schedules with HR and other trainers</li>\r\n<li>Preparing training materials with Manulife team</li>\r\n<li>Help to build up product structure to fit with customer needs (Loan/Deposit) and present to Manager&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Assist to develop tools, process, and procedure for front lines&rsquo; sales with more chances to obtain qualified referrals</li>\r\n<li>Consolidate weekly/monthly referrals report from all branches.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul class=\"bullet-red\">\r\n<li>Bachelor degree in Finance &amp; Banking, Sale &amp; Marketing Analysis, Business Administration or relevant degrees&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Minimum 2-3 year working experiences in business development &amp; support (life insurance is more preferred)</li>\r\n<li>Life insurance product knowledge is a plus</li>\r\n<li>Knowledge of training methods and techniques</li>\r\n<li>Ability to manage training arrangement &amp; schedules</li>\r\n<li>Computer literacy (good at excel), Good at PowerPoint &amp; Presentation skills</li>\r\n<li>Strong organizational and team management skills</li>\r\n<li>Good speaking &amp; writing in English</li>\r\n<li>Demonstrated knowledge of business and product development in insurance business is a plus.\r\n<h3>Location</h3>\r\n<p class=\"bodytext\">Head Office, Phnom Penh (1 post).</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>',1,41,15,'1','08/31/2018',0,NULL,3,5,4,'English','2018-07-29 11:55:45','2018-07-29 11:55:45'),
	(327,16,'Deputy Head of Payment and Fixed Asset Management Unit - 01 post','<ul class=\"bullet-red\">\r\n<li>Provide report related to payment of branchesUpload the transaction.</li>\r\n<li>Check the payment report prepared by finance officer before submit to management team.</li>\r\n<li>Identify the key product of each branch and report to management team for their attention.</li>\r\n<li>Assist management to daily, monthly and yearly analyze the bank payment as a whole.</li>\r\n<li>Analyze the variance of the cash &amp; cash equivalent and liabilities position from day to day and report to management team for any negative affect.</li>\r\n<li>Negotiate with other bank to place the deposit with ensure that high benefit is obtained and report to management for final decision.</li>\r\n<li>Monthly prepare the branch payment reportMonthly prepare average interest rate for deposit product.</li>\r\n<li>Verify the Advance settlement of the branches.</li>\r\n<li>Work closely and directly with the payment to ensure that report is properly prepared and submitted timely.</li>\r\n<li>Communicate to branch level to clarify any suspected points.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul class=\"bullet-red\">\r\n<li>Minimum 2 years of experience in Finance related field and especially in banking industry.</li>\r\n<li>Knowledge and experience in accounting and core banking system.</li>\r\n<li>Knowledge in Cambodian Accounting Standard (CAS) and Cambodian International Financial Reporting Standards (CIFRS).</li>\r\n<li>Knowledge and experience in preparing financial reports.</li>\r\n<li>Management and leadership skills.</li>\r\n<li>High teamwork spirit.</li>\r\n<li>Accounting and bookkeeping skills.</li>\r\n<li>Analytical, problem solving and reconciliation skills.</li>\r\n<li>Effective verbal and written communication skills.</li>\r\n<li>Good language skills in Khmer and English.</li>\r\n<li>Able to work under pressure and possess good time management.</li>\r\n<li>Professional accountant ethics.\r\n<h3>