	(383,15,'Deputy Director of Project Management Office - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Assist Director of Project Management Office (PMO) to define overall governance process of project management across the company.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Assist VP &amp; Director of PMO to track, analyze, and report progress of key project portfolio.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Assist VP &amp; Director of PMO to coordinate across key stakeholders to ensure effective changes &amp; collaboration in the organization</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Assist VP &amp; Director of PMO to manage communication across organization to support programs or project implementation; including presentation to stakeholders throughout project cycle.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Undertake different role(s) within project management Depending on nature of each project:<br />- Primary role is to lead/manage transformative project to align with corporate strategic direction; the role&nbsp; requires end-to-end management of project delivery which include business development, activity planning, risk/benefit identification, cross functional coordination, and effective project closure monitoring.<br />- As and when required, perform business analyst role to support functional teams<br /></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Foster a collaborative working environment with functional teams&nbsp;</span></li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Degree in business or related field is preferred</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Good proficiency in MS. Office including Ms. Excel , Ms. PowerPoint</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">At least 5 years experiences in project management or relevant experiences</span></li